The Office of the First Lady has announced that Melania Trump will be going on a three-state tour to promote her initiative, Be Best. The tour will include visits to Oklahoma, Washington State, and Nevada. In Oklahoma, she will visit an elementary school that focuses on character education. In Washington State, she will visit a tech company to learn about programs that teach online safety and help children with disabilities. In Nevada, she will participate in an opioids town hall. Melania Trump stated that Be Best aims to address the challenges faced by children in areas such as social media, technology, and drug abuse.